# Caddy reverse proxy for Beacon — terminates TLS (auto Let's Encrypt) and
# proxies to the Bun server on localhost:8080.
# Install to /etc/caddy/Caddyfile, then: sudo systemctl reload caddy
#
# The host below is the interim production hostname. Beacon's first integration
# target is vodshorter, so it lives at a subdomain of vodshorter.com until a
# dedicated short domain is chosen — then replace this host (or add the new one
# as a second site block) and `systemctl reload caddy`. The host's A record must
# point at the droplet BEFORE Caddy starts, so the ACME HTTP/TLS-ALPN challenge
# resolves.
#
# No on-disk access log block on purpose: Caddy's apt systemd unit ships with
# ProtectSystem hardening that blocks writes to /var/log/caddy without a
# ReadWritePaths override. Use journald instead: sudo journalctl -u caddy -f
beacon.vodshorter.com {
	reverse_proxy localhost:8080
	encode gzip zstd
	header -Server
}
